I"â<p>Contributing to the DevGrow community is easy.  Simply:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Fork the <a href="https://github.com/mdolon/devgrow">GitHub repository</a></li>
  <li>Read over the README.md, especially the Post Guidelines section</li>
  <li>Add your post to the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">_posts</code> directory and upload any relevant assets</li>
  <li>Commit your changes</li>
  <li>Make a Pull Request</li>
</ol>

<p>While anyone is welcome to author a post and make a pull request, all articles published must meet the following criteria:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Content must be relevant to the subject matters covered by this blog</li>
  <li>Content must be free of any and all advertisements to third party websites</li>
  <li>Content must be free of obscenity and anything graphic in nature</li>
  <li>Content must be original and available exclusively on DevGrow.com</li>
</ul>

<p>If this criteria is met, your pull request will be accepted and your article published.</p>
